    "summary": "Entrepreneurship is the <strong>single biggest cluster on the Entrepreneurship ICDC exam</strong>, worth roughly <strong>14 of every 100 questions</strong>. It tests the whole arc of starting a venture: spotting an unmet need, validating it, assessing start-up requirements and risks, deciding when to hire and what equipment to buy, and eventually exiting. Expect plain scenario questions about <strong>feasibility studies, entrepreneurial discovery, capital resources, and the traits/roles of the entrepreneur</strong>, plus one or two simple percentage-math items.",
