          "<strong>Start-up requirements (time, money, licensing fees) depend on the nature of the business.</strong> Expect a simple math item: divide the cost by total start-up costs to get a percentage. Example tested: an $11,250 licensing fee on $75,000 total start-up = <strong>15%</strong>. Practice this division so it's automatic.",
          "A core money-saving move when selecting <strong>capital resources</strong> (equipment, machinery, fixtures) is to <strong>buy used equipment</strong> — heavily discounted but still functional. DECA rejects 'buy as little as possible' because the right equipment matters to success.",
