          "<strong>Productivity</strong> is output per worker per period. The factor that most reduces it in a new venture is <strong>poor communication</strong> — if management never communicates goals, processes, and expectations, employees can't perform, and lower productivity drags down customer satisfaction.",
          "<strong>Operating procedures</strong> are step-by-step processes employees follow so routine tasks are done in a <strong>standard</strong> way. They cut down the time the owner spends answering repeat questions. The answer to 'tasks are performed in a ___ way' is almost always <strong>standard/consistent</strong>."
